Document: First 3D Game: Jumping and Squashing Monsters
Path: godot/getting_started/first_3d_game/06.jump_and_squash.rst
Summary: This section explains how to implement jumping mechanics and squash enemies in a 3D game using Godot.

Inherits: KinematicBody (PhysicsBody, CollisionObject, Spatial, Node, Object)

This section covers adding jumping and enemy squashing mechanics to your 3D game.

Jumping Mechanics
To implement jumping, we'll modify the player's movement script.

Key Rule: The player should only be able to jump when they are on the floor.

We will use the `is_on_floor()` method to check if the player is grounded.

GDScript:
func _physics_process(delta):
	# Add the gravity.
	if not is_on_floor():
		velocity.y -= gravity * delta

	# Handle jump.
	if Input.is_action_just_pressed("jump") and is_on_floor():
		velocity.y = jump_velocity

	# Get the input direction and handle the movement/deceleration.
	# As good practice, you should replace UI actions with custom gameplay actions.
	var direction = Vector3.ZERO
	if Input.is_action_pressed("move_forward"):
		direction.z -= 1
	if Input.is_action_pressed("move_backward"):
		direction.z += 1
	if Input.is_action_pressed("move_left"):
		direction.x -= 1
	if Input.is_action_pressed("move_right"):
		direction.x += 1

	velocity.x = direction.x * SPEED
	velocity.z = direction.z * SPEED

	move_and_slide()

Enemy Squashing
To make the player squash enemies when jumping on them, we need to detect when the player collides with an enemy from above.

We can achieve this by checking the relative position of the player and the enemy during a collision.

GDScript:
func _on_Player_body_entered(body):
	if body.is_in_group("enemies"):
		# Check if the player is moving downwards and is above the enemy
		if velocity.y < 0 and global_transform.origin.y > body.global_transform.origin.y:
			body.queue_free() # Remove the enemy
			velocity.y = jump_velocity # Give the player a small boost upwards
		else:
			# Player hit the enemy from the side or below, take damage or lose
			pass # Implement player damage or game over logic here

This setup allows for a common platformer mechanic where players can defeat enemies by jumping on their heads.

Note: Ensure your enemy nodes are added to the "enemies" group in the Godot editor for this script to work correctly.

Tip: You can adjust the `jump_velocity` and the downward velocity check to fine-tune the feel of the jump and squash interaction.
